// EXPECT_ERROR: extern byVal class
// EXPECT_ERROR: Beguile can't insert copy-in code
//
// `extern byVal class Foo` is rejected: extern means the class is defined in I6
// source, and the copy-in machinery (operator= dispatch at every call site of
// every function taking Foo) can't be inserted into call sites Beguile doesn't
// generate. The marker only makes sense for classes Beguile fully owns.
#beguilerSettings { target = z5; informName = "none"; outputPath = "tests/output"; }
extern byVal class Foo {
    int x;
}
void main(){}
